        &lt;h2&gt;Blues&lt;span class=&#34;hx-absolute -hx-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;blues&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#blues&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Music cal led BLUES has long been a part of the of American musical heritage. We find it in the music of many popular song writers, in ballads, boogie and rock. Blues follows a basic formula, that is, a standard chord progression:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4 measures of the I chord&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 measures of the IV chord&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 measures of the I chord&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 measure of the $V^7$ chord&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 measures of the IV chord&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 measures of the I chord&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

      </description>
